list.name: Default
list.comment: Renamed node project (and directory). Added several testing frameworks and test files for Node. Added initial configuration file for Angular tests.

task.summary: All server-side componenets required to begin developing on the front-end have been added. Only functional modules are index, users, and asset. Ready to implement "create" and "select" modules on front-end.
Allows sign-in/sign-up capabilities. sent to a home screen after signing in or signing up. Also added CSS styles in.
Now able to create and update Properties. Asset list has been modified to only display properties. Next step is to display a "saved" message after clicking save.

Rather than completely re-populating the Asset screens when a property/deal record is modified or created, only the updated/created asset record is "re-pushed" to the item list and updated. Easier for users. Next step is the Activities section.

Modified the data model to allow for easier querying of property/deal specific information for assets and financials information for activities. Also added the "DeepPopulate" plugin for Mongoose to greatly simplify deep querying. Next step is the Reporting module.
Added Reporting module (D3 chart) that automatically updates data. Next step is to add comments, error handling, and unit testing.
